abstract: >
  BlogPilot AI is an open-source, self-hostable SEO content studio that replaces premium tools
  (Surfer SEO, Ahrefs, Clearscope, Screaming Frog, AlsoAsked, MarketMuse) with a single application
  the user runs locally. It uses one AI API key (free Google Gemini is sufficient) plus free public
  endpoints (Bing SERP, Google Autocomplete, Wikipedia, PageSpeed Insights, OpenStreetMap).
  Features include real-time content scoring against top-10 SERP, a 28-rule technical SEO crawler,
  PAA tree explorer, SERP feature detector, topic authority scorer via Wikipedia, AI Overviews
  citation optimizer, llms.txt generator, hreflang manager, and 7 CMS export formats including
  WordPress XML and Ghost JSON. The Methodology Library ships 45 versioned playbooks codifying
  current Google Helpful Content, E-E-A-T, and AI Overview citation patterns.
